President Trump held a Cabinet meeting to discuss various domestic policy issues. He provided updates on the current state of the economy, highlighting low unemployment rates, soaring stock market levels, and GDP growth. He emphasized the need for tax cuts to further stimulate economic growth. The President also expressed his desire to reduce government spending and implement welfare reform. He addressed the issue of rising prescription drug prices and called for fair pricing practices. Additionally, he discussed immigration reform, the need for border security, and the nomination of Kirstjen Nielsen as Secretary of the Department of Homeland Security. The President also mentioned recent natural disasters and tragedies, such as the wildfires in California and the mass shooting in Las Vegas. He urged Congress to confirm his nominees and criticized the Democrats for obstructing the nomination process. Finally, he discussed the Iran Deal, healthcare reform, and Steve Bannon's criticism of the Republican establishment.